---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
	<BaseHead title={`Our Bread | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
</head>

<body>
	<Header />

	<main>
		<section class="content">
  			<h1>Our Bread</h1>

  			<p>
    			Bread is one of humanity's oldest foods. Flour, water, salt, and time are
    			simple ingredients, yet together they create something extraordinary.
  			</p>

  			<p>
    			At Sonoran Rise Bakery, we believe exceptional bread begins long before the
    			dough is mixed. It starts with thoughtfully grown grain, careful milling,
    			and an understanding that great bread cannot be rushed. Every loaf is
    			mixed, fermented, shaped, and baked with intention.
  			</p>

 			 <p>
    			We specialize in naturally leavened sourdough made with heritage and
    			regionally inspired grains whenever possible. Long fermentation develops
    			flavor, improves texture, and allows each loaf to express the character of
    			the flour from which it was made.
  			</p>

			<p>
				We aren't interested in making bread as quickly as possible.
			</p>

			<p>
				<strong>We're interested in making bread worth slowing down for.</strong>
			</p>

			<hr>

			<h2>Our Philosophy</h2>

			<p>
				Good bread doesn't need a long list of ingredients.
			</p>

			<p>
				It needs good ingredients, careful hands, and patience.
			</p>

			<p>
				Our process favors time over shortcuts. Dough is allowed to ferment
				naturally, developing the complex flavors, open crumb, and crisp crust that
				define traditional artisan bread.
			</p>

			<p>
				Every loaf is shaped by hand.<br>
				Every loaf is unique.
			</p>

			<p>
				We believe those small differences are part of what makes handcrafted bread
				special.
			</p>

			<hr>

			<h2>Our Ingredients</h2>

			<p>
				We keep our ingredient list intentionally short.
			</p>

			<ul>
				<li>Flour</li>
				<li>Water</li>
				<li>Salt</li>
				<li>Natural sourdough starter</li>
			</ul>

			<p>
				Whenever possible, we seek out exceptional grains that tell the story of
				the people, culture, and region of the Sonoran Desert. We are especially passionate about
				heritage wheats and supporting the farmers, millers, and researchers
				preserving their remarkable flavors and histories.
			</p>

			<p>
				Because great bread deserves great grain.
			</p>

			<hr>

			<h2>What You Can Expect</h2>

			<p>
				When you bring home a loaf from Sonoran Rise, we hope you'll notice more
				than its appearance.
			</p>

			<ul>
				<li>Smell the aroma released when the loaf is cut.</li>
				<li>Feel the texture of a well-developed crust.</li>
				<li>Slow down and enjoy the first bite.</li>
			</ul>

			<p>
				Bread has a way of bringing people together around a table, slowing down an
				otherwise busy day, and reminding us that simple things—made well—are often
				the most memorable.
			</p>

			<p>
				<strong>That is the experience we strive to create with every loaf.</strong>
			</p>
			</section>
	</main>

	<Footer />
</body>
</html>